        "comments": [
          {
            "row_reference": "Row 126",
            "row_number": "126",
            "comment": "BIS label for rack server modules is not placed on the product, but instead on the shipping label. From Hung Vuong - I researched the missing BIS compliance logo issue for both sale orders 110428076 and 110428072 with the product UCSB-B200-M5-U. I rooted the issue to the current Cisco’s internal applications not flagging for the India MRP carton label. It was designed a while back to flag the India carton label only for certain India booking entities and not ship-to India country. Therefore, the India label was not flagged as yes to print for the sale orders 110428076 and 110428072. The issue is within Cisco’s internal applications. I did not find any issues associated with the fulfillment Mfg partner FTX site or their label printing program. Issue: Missing BIS logo on the Cisco’s packaging labels. The fix is targeted by late July 2020… The supply chain’s GCCB project team and the India compliance team are currently working on the fix. Avi is the project PM driving it currently. The fix will enhance the existing logic to trigger based on the ship-to India country for the India MRP carton label to print regardless of the booking entity. It’s targeted to go live for some high priority DF sites [FTX and some others] by late July 2020. I looped in Stenish to seek support for the short term rework process if both sale orders are stuck at India custom currently. Stenish and his team can support from Cisco’s India operation for the short term rework process to clear customs if required. References of impacted sale orders: 110428076 SS #2 Line #1 ... FTX PID: UCSB-B200-M5-U <<< Has India BIS compliance number R-41004530 Status: Shipped ... May 28, 2020 110428072 SS #2 Line #1 & 2 ... FTX PID: UCSB-B200-M5-U <<< Has India BIS compliance number R-41004530 Status: Shipped ... May 28, 2020",
            "author": "Brent Taira",
            "created_at": "06/25/20 6:22 PM"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "comment": "Switches are not in BIS scope. PSU with Switch Mode with output voltage 48V are exempted. Power supply shipped fitted with main equipment does not fall under BIS scope.",
